article.headline: Georgia Southern 107, UT-Chattanooga 84
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. (AP) -- Georgia Southern nailed a Southern Conference record 22 three-pointers, 11 by Elton Nesbitt, as the Eagles cruised to a 107-84 victory over Chattanooga Monday night. The Eagles (9-7, 4-2 SoCon) equaled the eighth-highest single game total in NCAA Division I history and most this year by any Division I team. Nesbitt set a school record by tying the season's best in Division I, and his career-high 43 points equaled the highest individual total this year. Nesbitt scored 20 of Georgia Southern's first 29 points en route to a 53-38 halftime lead. He finished 15-of-21 from the field, 11-of-16 from long distance, and hit both free throws two days after scoring 39 points two days earlier against Appalachian State. Terry Williams would have tied the Eagles' 3-point record without Nesbitt's record night. Williams had a season-high 26 points, hitting eight 3s in 13 attempts. Alphonso Pugh and Matt Malone led Chattanooga in scoring with 26 and 10 points, respectively.
